summary: so I just bought a new amiibo for Smash (Ryu, specifically) for those who don’t know, the whole shtick with Smash amiibos is...
body:
so I just bought a new amiibo for Smash (Ryu, specifically)

for those who don’t know, the whole shtick with Smash amiibos is that they’re basically trainable AIs. Fresh out of the box, you get a wimpy AI that has no idea how to do anything - but, the more it battles, the more it learns, and if trained well enough it will eventually surpass level 9 CPUs and the most powerful human opponents.

anyway the reason I bring this up is because Ryu here, fresh out of the box, in his very first fight, against a level 9 CPU, somehow managed to land a KO.

he lost the fight overall, as expected. but the fact that he managed to knock out the level 9 CPU even once with zero experience is still impressive.

I have a good feeling about this boy. I think he will be a formidable rival to my other amiibo-collecting Smash friend.
